description:
We're happy to announce that our first blood drive of the semester on campus is scheduled on September 13th and 14th at the Yard on College Avenue. We feel great pride that Rutger's UBI is able to help in this beautiful drive hosted by Robert Wood Johnson Barnabas Health. Today, the country confronts new challenges that disrupt the blood supply. As concerns compound, blood centers nationwide are facing a decline in donor turnout, and donor eligibility misinformation. Yet the need for blood remains constant. We need youth like you to donate and save a life! 

Donors will receive a $5 coffee gift card, a jersey mikes sub, a t-shirt, and a chance to win 1 out of 4 $25 WaWa Gift cards!
name: Blood Drive

description:
Please sign up here: https://forms.gle/LXoA5Ym2qZ65SBcY9
 
As a volunteer, you'll have the opportunity to be a part of the exciting and fast-paced action that is dragon boat racing. You'll also get to experience the energy and excitement of the festival event atmosphere and be a part of a vibrant community of dragon boat enthusiasts. Volunteers will be needed to help with various tasks in ensuring the safety and smooth operations of the event through the various outlined tasks:
 

Volunteer Roles Need:

  • Boat Marshalls- will be on the dock assisting paddlers with getting in and out of the boats. This position should be filled by people who are comfortable around water.
  • Results Runners- will be posting the results from the Timing Officials at the Registration Headquarters. This position requires neat handwriting.
  • Team Marshalls- will assist the Marshalling Manager in ensuring that all teams are ready to load into boats at the correct time to maintain smooth running of the raves.
  • Crowd Control- will ensure one-way flow traffic from the Marshaling Area after boats are unloaded.
All Volunteers will receive:
  • Volunteer Hours (if applicable)
  • Free shirt
  • Free Lunch and Drinks
  • Opportunity to ride in a dragon boat
  • Opportunity to make new friends and have fun
Basic Event Info:
Location: Mercer County Park, east of the Marina at 334 S Post Rd, West Windsor Twp, NJ 08691
Date: Saturday, 9/16/23
Time: Pickups starts at 6am, Event is 7am-5pm
 
Sign-ups will be first-come first-serve.
Form closes 9/14/23
Ride Groups will be created after sign-ups close.
 
Expect to spend most of the day with us.
Hats and Sunscreen are recommended
name: Dragon Boat Volunteering

description:
Join us for an exhilarating start to the Fall 2023 semester at the RU SOARS Kickoff event! Get ready to embark on a journey of academic excellence and community building. Whether you're a returning student or new to Rutgers University, this event is designed to ignite your passion for learning and foster connections with fellow scholars.

Date: Wednesday, September 20 Time: 7:30 PM - 8:30 PM Location: Douglass Student Center, Room E

Highlights of the event include:

  • Welcome Address: Inspirational words from generals members, setting the tone for a successful semester.
  • Student Success Workshops: Engage in interactive sessions for academic achievement and personal growth.
  • Meet and Greet: Forge new friendships and professional relationships in a relaxed and friendly atmosphere.
  • Resource Fair: Explore the wealth of campus resources, from academic support to extracurricular opportunities.
  • Refreshments: Enjoy light snacks as you mingle with peers and explore the event offerings.

Whether you're eager to dive into studies, engage in campus life, or find support for success, the RU SOARS Fall 2023 Semester Kickoff has something for everyone. Let's embark on this academic journey together!
